  "text": "In 2009, the results of a landmark trial [CITATION_1] were reported, comparing the pulsatile, first-generation HeartMate XVE with the CF HeartMate II device. The study included 200 patients with a left ventricular ejection fraction of less than 25%, peak oxygen consumption of less than 14 mL/kg/min, NYHA class IIIB or IV symptoms, or the need for an intra-aortic balloon pump or inotropic therapy. Actuarial survival was significantly improved in the HeartMate II group compared to the HeartMate XVE group (68% versus 55%, resp., at 1 year and 58% versus 24% at 2 years; Figure 3 ). Adverse event rates were also significantly reduced with the HeartMate II (Figure 4) .",
